# Cinemachine (CM3)

## Policy

- **All gameplay cameras** use Cinemachine 3 (`Unity.Cinemachine`), not manual `Camera.transform` animation.
- **Main Camera** keeps `Camera`, `AudioListener`, URP `UniversalAdditionalCameraData`, and **`CinemachineBrain`**.
- Virtual cameras: **`CinemachineCamera`** + body/aim components (`CinemachineFollow`, `CinemachineRotationComposer`, …).
- Follow targets: assign `CinemachineCamera.Target.TrackingTarget` / `LookAtTarget` to the **Player root** (or `MenuShowcase` in MainMenu). Use [`GameplayCameraBinder`](Assets/Game/Scripts/Runtime/Gameplay/Cameras/GameplayCameraBinder.cs) when binding at runtime.
- Do **not** add a `CameraTarget` child — visual bob stays on `Model`; Player root Y is physics-stable.

## Scene layout

```
--- CAMERAS ---
  Main Camera       # Brain + Unity Camera
  GameCamera        # CinemachineCamera (default vcam)
  CameraBinder      # GameplayCameraBinder → Player / MenuShowcase
```

Reuse [`Prefabs/Cameras/`](Assets/Game/Prefabs/Cameras/) for level scenes. Rig prefab leaves `_followTarget` null; scene instances wire Player.

## Code

- Namespace: `Game.Gameplay.Cameras`
- Assembly: `Game.Gameplay` → reference `Unity.Cinemachine`
- Do **not** use CM2 types (`CinemachineVirtualCamera`, `CinemachineFreeLook` legacy API).

## 2D

Orthographic projects: set lens on `CinemachineCamera`; see `unity-2d.mdc`.

## MCP

- Tool group: **core** (default on)
- Tool: `manage_camera` — prefers Cinemachine when package installed (`ping` → `cinemachine: true`)
- Actions: `create_camera`, `set_target`, `set_lens`, `set_priority`, `list_cameras`
- After MCP camera edits: `read_console` + verify Brain on Main Camera

